# Browserslist configuration
# Defines the supported browser baseline. Consumed by eslint-plugin-compat
# (which fails lint if src/ uses an API/syntax above this floor) and the
# `browserslist` npm scripts.
#
# Strategy: Target all in-use browsers (defaults) that support BigInt (hard requirement).
#
# There is no transpile step — the source is authored to stay within what
# these browsers already support, rather than being compiled down to them.
#
# "defaults" = > 0.5% usage, last 2 versions, Firefox ESR, not dead
# Filtering by "supports bigint" excludes KaiOS 2.5 and Opera Mini (can't run BigInt)
#
# This query targets all in-use browsers with BigInt support. Run
# `npx browserslist --coverage` to see the current global-coverage percentage.
# See: https://github.com/browserslist/browserslist#queries

# Target all in-use browsers that can run BigInt (non-polyfillable)
defaults and supports bigint
